[0m[49m[39m  159, 161[0m:[39m[49m ### Prerequisites
[0m[49m[39m  160, 162[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[39m  161, 163[0m:[39m[49m | Requirement | Details |
[0m[49m[39m  162, 164[0m:[39m[49m |-------------|---------|
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 163     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m | **AWS Services** | Amazon Neptune, AWS AppSync, AWS Lambda, Amazon S3, Amazon DynamoDB, AWS PrivateLink, AWS Organizations, Amazon CloudWatch, AWS CloudTrail |
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 164     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m | **IAM Permissions** | `neptune-db:*` (scoped to cluster), `appsync:GraphQL`, `lambda:InvokeFunction`, `s3:GetObject`, `dynamodb:GetItem`, `dynamodb:Query` |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      165[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | **AWS Services** | Amazon Neptune, AWS AppSync, AWS Lambda, Amazon S3, Amazon DynamoDB, AWS PrivateLink, AWS Organizations, Amazon CloudWatch, AWS CloudTrail, AWS KMS, Amazon API Gateway |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      166[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | **IAM Permissions** | Federation layer (read-only): `neptune-db:ReadDataViaQuery`, `neptune-db:GetQueryStatus`, `neptune-db:CancelQuery` (scoped to cluster ARN). Write access to Neptune remains with each institution's internal data pipeline roles only. Additional: `appsync:GraphQL`, `lambda:InvokeFunction`, `s3:GetObject`, `dynamodb:GetItem`, `dynamodb:Query` |
[0m[49m[39m  165, 167[0m:[39m[49m | **BAA** | AWS BAA signed for all participating accounts (knowledge derived from PHI requires BAA coverage) |
[0m[49m[39m  166, 168[0m:[39m[49m | **Encryption** | Neptune: encryption at rest (enabled at cluster creation, cannot be added later); S3: SSE-KMS; DynamoDB: encryption at rest; all cross-account traffic over PrivateLink (TLS in transit) |
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 167     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m | **VPC** | Each institution's Neptune in a private subnet. PrivateLink endpoints for cross-account access. No public endpoints. VPC Flow Logs enabled. |
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 168     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m | **CloudTrail** | Enabled in all participating accounts. Federated query audit trail must capture: requester identity, query content, sources contacted, results returned. |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      169[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | **VPC** | Each institution's Neptune in a private subnet. PrivateLink endpoints for cross-account access. No public endpoints. VPC Flow Logs enabled. Gateway VPC endpoints for S3 and DynamoDB in the federation control plane VPC. Interface VPC endpoints for KMS and CloudWatch Logs. No NAT Gateway required for federation Lambda functions. |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      170[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | **CloudTrail** | Enabled in all participating accounts. Federated query audit trail must capture: requester identity, query content (treated as PHI), sources contacted, results returned. Audit log access restricted to authorized compliance personnel. |
[0m[49m[39m  169, 171[0m:[39m[49m | **Multi-Account** | AWS Organizations with one account per participating institution. Cross-account IAM roles for federation layer access. |
[0m[49m[39m  170, 172[0m:[39m[49m | **Sample Data** | Public biomedical ontologies (SNOMED CT subset, RxNorm, DrugBank open data) for development. Never use institution-specific clinical knowledge in shared dev environments. |
[0m[49m[39m  171, 173[0m:[39m[49m | **Cost Estimate** | Neptune: ~$0.35/hr per instance (db.r5.large) per institution. Lambda: negligible at query volumes. PrivateLink: $0.01/GB + $0.01/hr per endpoint. Total: ~$2,500-5,000/month per participating node. |
